      "category": "creatures",
      "entity_domain": "fauna",
      "entity_subtype": "creature",
      "excerpt": "A heat-adapted amphibian observed near volcanic vents in Light No Fire, known for its ember-patterned dorsal scales.",
      "body_html_sanitized": "<p>The <strong>Ember Salamander</strong> is documented by explorers along basalt ridges where ground heat keeps small pools warm year-round.</p><p>Its orange dorsal pattern may help it blend with glowing ember cracks during night foraging.</p><ul><li>Habitat: volcanic foothills</li><li>Behavior: nocturnal foraging</li><li>Threat: low to explorers</li></ul>",
